data.text:
Dinah Shore (1916-1994) was an actress and singer who had a long career in television, recordings, and public appearances. She had two #1 singles in the 1940s: "I'll Walk Alone", and "Buttons and Bows".

Her daytime talk show Dinah! featured several appearances by the Muppets. She also released a Sesame Street album in 1979, Dinah! I've Got a Song.

Shore also appeared alongside Earl Sinclair in an ABC promo for Dinosaurs, mistakenly believing her own show is being brought back for a new season.

References[]

During the opening "We're in Charge" number of Out to Lunch, Bert mentions a potential grievance for the viewing audience toward the network is that they "verged on treason when they cancelled Dinah Shore."
